<title>NETHERLANDS: Unions said to seek KLM dividend freeze.</title>
<headline>Unions said to seek KLM dividend freeze.</headline>
<dateline>AMSTERDAM 1997-04-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Unions representing KLM workers have said the Dutch airline should temporarily stop paying dividends to shareholders, the Dutch news agency ANP reported on Thursday.</p>
<p>ANP said the FNV and CNV Transport unions were calling for a temporary freeze on dividend payments, so shareholders would also bear part of the burden of the airline's drive to cut costs and boost operating profits.</p>
<p>The agency said union leaders and KLM management would meet again on May 2 to discuss the Focus 2000 plan, which is aimed at making KLM more profitable.</p>
<p>-- Amsterdam newsroom +31 20 504 5000</p>
